 from fisheries to banking, Earnest illustrates the promise of computer models for explaining the surprises, cascades, and complexity that characterize global politics today. These examples of massively parallel globalization contrast sharply with the hierarchical and inflexible governmental bureaucracies that are poorly suited to solve many of today's transnational and global challenges.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aGlobalizationxPolitical aspects. 0aPolitical sociology. 0aSocial networksxPolitical aspects. 0aWorld politicsx21st century. 0aWorld politicsy21st century. 4aBusiness and Economics : Economy and Society. 4aPolitics and Law : Political Science. 4aPolitics and Law : Political Sociology. 4aSociology : Social Movements. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Globalization.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2015z978311149061840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438456621423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438456621/original  a978-3-11-149061-8  SUNY Press eBook Package 2015b2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles